text: as a food lover along with eating
visiting a local Fresh Market is one of
my favorite things to do in any city
Kuala Lumpur largest wet market is known
as Chao kit market a colorful display of
the diverse selection of ingredients
used in Malaysian cuisine twelvers cow's
head target and it's one of the largest
fresh wet markets in the city and they
have a lot of my absolute favorite
ingredients in the entire world these
aisles pet eye or stink beans as they're
commonly known is one of my absolute
favorite foods on the planet and at
Chowk it they hang from the rafters
everywhere fruits vegetables herbs
spices seafood and meat are all
available in large quantities throughout
the market
so next time you're in KL take a morning
to walk around Chowk it for a
fascinating glimpse into the local
market life and like any market in the
world be careful with your belongings
and if possible go with a friend
